							<div class="post_wrapper author">
								<div id="about_the_author">
									<div class="gravatar"><a href="https://lithub.com/author/alecnevalalee/"><img src="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/alecnevalalee-100x100.jpg" width="100" height="100" srcset="https://s26162.pcdn.co/wp-content/uploads/2025/06/alecnevalalee-300x300.jpg 2x" alt="Alec Nevala-Lee" class="avatar avatar-100 wp-user-avatar wp-user-avatar-100 alignnone photo" /></a></div>
									<div class="description author withsidebar">
										<h6><a href="https://lithub.com/author/alecnevalalee/">Alec Nevala-Lee</a></h6>
										Alec Nevala-Lee is the author of <em>Inventor of the Future: The Visionary Life of Buckminster Fuller</em> and the Hugo Award finalist <em>Astounding: John W. Campbell, Isaac Asimov, Robert A. Heinlein, L. Ron Hubbard, and the Golden Age of Science Fiction</em>. His nonfiction has appeared in print and online in such publications as the <em>New York Times</em>, the <em>Atlantic</em>, <em>Slate</em>, <em>Salon</em>, and the <em>Daily Beast</em>. He lives with his wife, the NPR host Wailin Wong, and their daughter in Oak Park, Illinois.																			</div>
